sequenceDiagram
    participant User as External User
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>Edge Termination
    participant Service as model-registry Service<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuthProxy as OAuth Proxy Container<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuth as OpenShift OAuth Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant REST as REST Container<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant DB as PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>5432/3306 TLS Optional

    Note over User,DB: Flow 1: External User Access (OAuth Mode)

    User->>Router: POST /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/models<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Router->>Route: Forward Request<br/>HTTPS/443
    Route->>Service: Edge Termination<br/>HTTPS/8443
    Service->>OAuthProxy: Bearer Token Validation<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS1.2+
    OAuthProxy->>OAuth: Validate Token<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Service Account Token
    OAuth-->>OAuthProxy: Token Valid<br/>User Identity
    OAuthProxy->>REST: Forward Request<br/>HTTP/8080 (localhost)
    REST->>DB: Query ML Metadata<br/>Username/Password<br/>TLS Optional
    DB-->>REST: Model Metadata
    REST-->>OAuthProxy: JSON Response
    OAuthProxy-->>Service: HTTPS Response
    Service-->>Route: Response
    Route-->>Router: Response
    Router-->>User: 200 OK<br/>Model Metadata JSON

    Note over User,DB: Flow 2: Internal Cluster Access (Non-OAuth Mode)

    participant InternalPod as Internal Pod
    participant ServiceHTTP as model-registry Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    InternalPod->>ServiceHTTP: GET /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/models<br/>No Auth
    ServiceHTTP->>REST: Forward Request<br/>HTTP/8080
    REST->>DB: Query ML Metadata<br/>Username/Password
    DB-->>REST: Model Metadata
    REST-->>ServiceHTTP: JSON Response
    ServiceHTTP-->>InternalPod: 200 OK

    Note over User,DB: Flow 3: Operator Reconciliation

    participant Controller as controller-manager
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Webhook as webhook-service<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch ModelRegistry CRs<br/>ServiceAccount Token<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: CR Created/Updated
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validate CR<br/>POST /validate-*<br/>Webhook Client Certificate
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Valid
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Service<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Route<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Resources Created

    Note over User,DB: Flow 4: Metrics Collection

    participant Prom as Prometheus
    participant MetricsSvc as controller-manager-metrics-service<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS

    Prom->>MetricsSvc: GET /metrics<br/>Bearer Token (ServiceAccount)<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS
    MetricsSvc-->>Prom: Prometheus Metrics
